@NODE 1.1. "Justification"


  Justification
================

Only ocasionally do I insert bitmap graphics in FinalWriter, but everytime
I do it I remember when the job gets printed that the aspect/ratio of the
screen graphics does not correspond with the printed one.

Tired of wasting my time waiting for my printed artwork, just to see that
the results does not match my desires, I finally decided to write a macro
that would solve this problem automatically with the click of a mouse.

And here it is for your use as well as mine.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 1.2. "Installation"


  Installation
===============

Just copy the file Adjust_pal (spanish) or Adjust_pal.english (english)
into FinalWriter/FWMacros.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 1.3. "Usage"


  Usage
========

Start FinalWriter, import your bitmaps and select them, then you must
load the file previously copied, from the menu

   	User/Other/Arexx Script...

The script will give you three choices:

Cancel ========= If you need an explanation, you'd better buy a peessee.

Shorter ======== Decreases 10 % of graphic's height.

Wider ========== Increases graphic's width by 10 %.


And that's all, the bitmap and EPS graphics will get the transformation
you choose, and will be redrawn.


@ENDNODE

